content: Good time killer

THIS is what tower defense games should be. As someone who played custom WC3 maps for years, I've been disgusted by what passes for a "tower defense" game these days. Element TD was one of the best, and this mobile edition just proves how far behind all of the modern TD games are. This game actually requires you to think and plan, which gives it depth. It might be missing multiplayer from the original, but this is hours of fun and for $1 with zero ads this is a steal. Quick not for the developer, if they read this: My only complaint is that it's hard to reliably tap a square or tower sometimes, especially if it's behind a tower.

Great TD game. Definately worth the small cost to your wallet. There is only one thing that imo is preventing a full 5 star rating - an unfortunate lack of any ingame grind element. No tech trees, no additional tower unlocks, or bonus runes etc. You literally have access to every map, tower combination and feature from square 1. This is a shame really as the only replay factor is tied to you wanting to try a new tower combo, or beat your hi score. Really hope developers have some grindable elements to promote replay value on a roadmap. Cmon devs - look at Infinitode or Dungeon Defence for example :)

One of the best TD's ever created hands down. If you love TD's and your goal is to pass the time, you could not pick a better tower defense game. You can make this as hard or as easy on yourself as you like. The towers and upgrades are beautifully balanced. They are complex enough to merit studying how they work and how viable they are in different situations but are simple enough to not be frustrated in the process. I first fell in love with this game when it first came out on Warcraft 3 Custom Games and I have been waiting a long time for some beautiful person to make a version for mobile devices. My hats off to the developers for doing an unbelievably good job, a flawless transition from PC to Mobile.   The only thing that could make me love you more is if you guys made a mobile version of Wintermaul TD.

First off I would like to say that I'm a TD game enthusiast and expert, so when I found this game I just had to buy it. At first I was sceptical about it's replayability and difficulty, but after playing it over 10 times and only winning once and still enjoying comming back and trying to find a new way to win, I can safety say that this TD is brilliantly well made and definitely worth it's price. Warning: More casual players might not enjoy it's difficulty, but anyone wanting an actual challenge will enjoy.

I like this game quite a bit, the great amount of tower combinations really gets me thinking about which elements I should build in this match to get a setup that's balanced enough and there's plenty of viable strategies which is very nice. One issue I do have is the lack of other content. Two game modes and a handful of maps doesn't really give you a lot of ways to test your abilities. Furthermore I have an issue with the fast forward option.  Whenever you enter a menu while fast forward is on it resets the state to normal speed but the button still indicates being on fast forward,  this is fixed by pressing fat forward again as it will still indicate the fast forward state while now actually being on fast forward but it can be rather misleading.

replyContent: Currently towers have a set Target Priority depending on the type of tower that is Nearest, Furthest, Weakest, Toughest, First, Last, or Random. Thanks for your comments. For example, Mushroom tower will attack the Toughest creep first while Life tower will attack the Weakest creep first. I will look at how this can be more visible. Cheers
